## Run with the default UI (recommended)

This app ships with `langchain-ai/deep-agents-ui` as the default frontend.

```bash
# 1. Bootstrap the UI (clones into ./ui and writes ui/.env.local)
bash bootstrap_ui.sh

# 2. Terminal A ‚Äî start the agent backend (LangGraph server on :2024)
cp .env.example .env   # then edit .env
langgraph dev

# 3. Terminal B ‚Äî start the UI on :3000
cd ui
pnpm install           # or: npm install / yarn install
pnpm dev

# 4. Open http://localhost:3000
```

The UI connects to the backend over the LangGraph SDK via `ui/.env.local`
(`NEXT_PUBLIC_DEPLOYMENT_URL=http://127.0.0.1:2024`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_AGENT_ID=deepagent`).
Override `LANGGRAPH_URL`, `AGENT_ID`, or `DEEP_AGENTS_UI_REF` when re-running
`bootstrap_ui.sh` if your setup differs.

## Run without the UI (headless)

```bash
export ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=...
python smoke_test.py        # import-level sanity check
python agent.py             # invoke with a default message
```

## Skills layout

`skills/` mirrors the original `.claude/skills/` directory. DeepAgents loads
skills from this folder; refer to upstream DeepAgents docs for skill loading
semantics.

## Manual actions

See `../conversion_report.md` for the prioritized list. Common items:

- Implement tool stubs in `tools.py`.
- Wire MCP servers in `mcp_tools.py` after reviewing `.mcp.json`.
- Replace any `***REDACTED***` placeholders with environment variables.
- Run `bash bootstrap_ui.sh` once to materialize the `ui/` directory.

## Limitations

- `TeamCreate` / `SendMessage` peer-to-peer messaging from the original
  Harness is approximated by main-agent-mediated handoff. See
  `../conversion_report.md` for the lossiness summary.
- This app is generated. Re-running `harness2deepagents` writes to a new
  timestamped directory by default to avoid overwriting your edits.
- `smoke_test.py` does not call the model. Run an actual invocation in a
  controlled environment before relying on this app.
- `bootstrap_ui.sh` clones `langchain-ai/deep-agents-ui` from GitHub at
  emit time of *first run* ‚Äî it is not embedded in this generated bundle.
